======================================================================
EXPECTED CYCLE COUNTS FOR RANDOM TOURNAMENTS ON p VERTICES
======================================================================

  E[c_k] = C(p,k) * (k-1)! / 2^k
  (Each k-subset has E[(k-1)!/2^{k-1}] directed Ham. cycles,
   divided by... wait, need careful counting)

  In a random tournament on k vertices:
  E[#directed Ham cycles] = (k-1)! * (1/2)^k
  (Each of (k-1)! directed cycles has prob (1/2)^k of all edges present)

  p=7:
    k= 3: E[c_k] = C(7,3)=      35 * 0.2500 =             8.8
    k= 5: E[c_k] = C(7,5)=      21 * 0.7500 =            15.8
    k= 7: E[c_k] = C(7,7)=       1 * 5.6250 =             5.6

